So, my team is trying to use limelight to do pose estimation, and we’re getting this really weird bug where it kind of jumps across the screen each time we tell it to update the pose, slowly getting closer over time, but sometimes going way in the wrong direction.

Our current code can be found here: CODE

It’s not our limelight’s problem, web dashboard knows where we are, it’s just a problem with actually updating our odometry

Are you dealing with the fact that LimeLight returns a pose of (0, 0) 0° when it doesn’t see a tag? You need to check if it sees a tag before using the value.

It is normal that the pose will slowly update when your estimated pose is far from the vision measurement. You can tune how much it “trusts” vision measurements by tuning the SwervePoseEstimator’s standard deviations.
